values:
Okay, so I found my old Live Journal, which was sad and abandoned for a long time.

Updates - I'm living in a transitional housing situation where I ended up after a long and arduous mental health battle.&nbsp; I have a different boyfriend now than when I wrote in here a year ago.&nbsp; His name is Chris, and he's wonderful.&nbsp; I'm trying to go back to school this fall on short notice so that I can get my Special Educator's Credential.&nbsp; This week I will ask my conservator (for I'm under county conservatorship) whether I can get funds released to go to school in time to meet the deadline.&nbsp; I'm excited and nervous at the same time, hence the trouble sleeping which lead me to seek out Live Journal past my usual bed time.

That is all.&nbsp;

I woke up really hungry but I don't have much food.&nbsp; I'm out of raisins.&nbsp; I have cereal but no milk. Is it okay to eat rice krispies without milk?&nbsp; They are the generic kind but still show a recipe for krispie marshmallow treats, so I figure they're the real deal.

I have a few sunflower seeds.&nbsp; That's not so substantial, but it might tide me over.&nbsp; 

I'm trying desperately not to eat out too much.&nbsp; I did yesterday at Panda Express, which I'm starting to think is a disgusting place.&nbsp;

I'm waiting for my friend Sierra to take me to her church's Hawaiian luao (sp?) party.&nbsp; I just took a shower, and I cleaned off the gunky shiny stuff I had on my nails.&nbsp; It was chipping and I don't really need it.&nbsp; 

I still haven't finished this friggin assignment.&nbsp; Harrumph.&nbsp; I guess I'll e-mail Bill about it and maybe we can meet when I go up to MPC sometime next week.

My meds are still making me very tired even when I get up and exercise.&nbsp; I always feel like I need to sleep by the middle of the day.&nbsp; Argh.

I'm gradually getting ready to move.&nbsp; I've moved a bit of stuff down to the garage, and just now I went and got some boxes at the dollar store.&nbsp; I'm not exactly sure when I'm moving, since it will depend on when my landlady finds someone.&nbsp; I know it will be by the end of the month.&nbsp; 

At first, I was worried that I would get dependent on this "structure living" environment so that I would not learn the basics of taking care of myself.&nbsp; Finally, I've decided that even with this plan, there are ways that I can be responsible for myself.&nbsp; I can start small if I have to and work up.&nbsp; I can take on little responsiblities, little by little.&nbsp; Slowly but surely, I hope to get used to an organized and clean environment where my medication is consistent and my daily routine has some consistency as well.&nbsp; Once that happens, I might actually pull some of the loose ends together that have been hanging out there for a long time.&nbsp; I need to get a copy of my birth certificate and social security card and finally get a new copy of my state ID.&nbsp; Once all that happens, I can begin seriously considering if I want a job, if I want to continue with school or what.&nbsp; 

Another thing I need to make sure of is that I stay in charge of my own life.&nbsp; Despite the fact that others are helping me, I should still be the one to make decisions for myself.&nbsp; As a friend told me, if I hit a brick wall at 60 mph, I want to be the reason I did.

I'm probably the most disorganized person I know.&nbsp; Recently, I've lost my house keys (still haven't found them, but I'm using my spare key), left my cell phone at the OE on campus (but it was found and I'm getting it soon), almost left my laptop on the bust (flagged down the bus driver, who said they were considering selling, joking), either lost or got stolen about $80 from purse, and that's not all.&nbsp; I think I'm going crazy over this stuff.&nbsp; Oh, and I lost my bus pass, so now I have to pay $2 every time I take the bus.&nbsp; That might seem like not that much, but it sure adds up when it's your only mode of transit.&nbsp; 

I've recently been commiting to following an almost vegan diet.&nbsp; I still eat honey sometimes, and I have had some transgresions, such as eating some swiss cheese when they put it in my sandwich and even eating some cheese pizza.&nbsp; I'm gradually trying to cut that stuff out and go back to basics.&nbsp; After I get all that down, I plan to go back to my once healthy lifestyle.&nbsp; I'm going to cut out soda altogether, even my beloved rootbeer.&nbsp; 

Then today I got a haircut.&nbsp; They parted my hair on the left side instead of straight down the center.&nbsp; I'm going to see if I can actually live with that.&nbsp; Whenever they've done that in the past, I've always combed back, but I'll see what I can do.&nbsp; 

I had Mother's Day with my mom last weekend too.&nbsp; It turned out to be pretty easy taking the bus out to Carmel Valley.&nbsp; I used to do it all the time coming home from work in Marina, but I forgot about it.

That's about this for this update.&nbsp; I know it's rather random and probably has some misspelled words, but whatever.

I've been going along trying to salvage what I can out of my little attempt here at CSUMB, and in the middle of it all, I had a conversation with the professor whose class I've had to unfortunately withdraw from.&nbsp; Her own background is in educational psychology, and I had thought that was the same as school psychology, which was something I had researched previously but had decided wasn't for me.&nbsp; She told me it was actually different and more on the theoretical side of things, which was how this conversation came up.&nbsp; She had to go and help another student, but she said we could always continue the conversation later on.&nbsp; 

I started looking around online and couldn't find much since most of it seemed to intermingle it with careers in school psychology, which is not exactly what I have in mind.&nbsp; I must admit I'm not exactly sure what it is I have in mind, so I'm sure that doesn't help in searching around either.&nbsp; In any event, I did come across one program at the University of Albany that seems more along the lines of what I'm thinking about, basically educational psychology research.&nbsp; I e-mailed the person it said to contact if you had any questions, and I suppose if I get anything back that would be the first step in finding out anything about this at alll.&nbsp; At this point, I feel like any redirection is kind of like a stab in the dark.&nbsp; 

I started in the direction of Special Education not knowing exactly if it would be my cup of tea to start with.&nbsp; When I was at Santa Cruz, I went back and forth over many different options.&nbsp; The education department there was so limited and mostly just focused on basic single-subject or multiple-subject teaching that I couldn't get much information on anything else while I was there.&nbsp; They basically pushed me into the Special Education route, telling me how there was such a high demand and all the rest.&nbsp; I felt like it was a good choice, but I didn't know much about the field even back then.&nbsp; I started hanging out online in this little chatroom for people with ADD/ADHD and I felt comfortable with these people, but I'm not sure that's a clear indication that the field is best for me.

I'm meeting again with my advisor this afternoon and I suppose I'll work something out with him regarding the more immediate questions of how to finish up everything for this and last semester, and then, as he said earlier, I can figure out what direction I really would like to take.

Norma (my therapist) also is trying to get me to become more organized in terms of finances and personal organization in general.&nbsp; I suppose that will all have to be in order before I take any more big moves in any direction.&nbsp; I don't want to take a jump and then fall flat on my face again.

That's an old Offspring song from my youth.
&nbsp;
Well, I'm back -- that's a line from LOTR -- the last line.

I'm feeling so random.&nbsp; 

In the process of delaying and losing my sanity, I've delayed studying for a very important test -- the CSET -- subject test.&nbsp; I have to take the last two sections, and I feel utterly unprepared.&nbsp; I'm going to a study hall style study session today in a few hours.&nbsp; Hopefully, they can get me on track, and I can get prepared.&nbsp; I need to make flashcards and after that, stay focused.

Blah.
